A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This program, BA 4, PE 0603036F, Modular Advanced Missile (MAM) is not a new start.

 The Modular Advanced Missile Program Element provides linkage between Research & Development and fielding of weapons capabilities. It will analyze, develop,
 mature, and demonstrate new or emerging armament technologies, processes, interfaces, mission planning, special test equipment, and resources.

 This program invests in analytical, data management, digital environments, networks, facilities, and security infrastructure upgrades supporting development of this
 program's capabilities, while leveraging the Department of War (DoW) and the Department of the Air Force (DAF) enterprise IT solutions. Expands program office staff,
 facilities, and security infrastructure to support the required classification levels for this program's activities. Engages with DoW, DAF, and industry stakeholders to refine
 threat analysis, refine inventory requirements, and plan upgrade requirements. Capitalizes on and incorporates successful laboratory research and development efforts
 applicable to this program's capability.

 This program element included all necessary expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program funds would be in
 addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program elements 0605829F, 0605831F, 0605833F, and 0605898F.

 Project was previously funded in PE 0207325F, Joint Air-to-Surface Standoff Missile (JASSM), Project 675356, JASSM Extended Range (JASSM-ER) in FY2026 and
 prior.

 This effort is in Budget Activity 4, Advanced Component Development and Prototypes (ACD&P), because efforts are necessary to evaluate integrated technologies,
 representative modes or prototype systems in a high fidelity and realistic operating environment.




