C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                     FY 2025 FY 2026
Congressional Add: In-Transit Visibility (ITV) Modernization                                                               0.000  10.000
FY 2025 Accomplishments: Program Funded in FY 2026 as a Congressional Add.
FY 2026 Plans: The acquisition strategy is a three-phased approach.

Phase One, Requirements Gathering and Analysis:
This initial phase is focused on translating the broad challenges across the Joint Deployment and Distribution
Enterprise (JDDE) into specific, actionable, and measurable technical and operational requirements. The goal is
to establish a clear roadmap for development and to ensure alignment amongst the stakeholders' needs and the
proposed commercial solution. A worldwide ITV workshop conducted for 60 key stakeholders from the Services
and DLA, in addition to members across the JDDE. Through facilitated guided discussions, develop tangible
actionable plans and tasks that will lead to the modernized ITV system that will be a comprehensive ecosystem
of Remote Monitoring Devices (RMDs), including sensors, tags, and devices, tailored to specific use cases
and operating environments. Intended outcomes: Baseline ITV Terminology, Explore Necessary Operational
Elements and Capabilities, Define Technology Features and/or Configurations, Draft Specific Tagging Protocols
and Process, Consider Future Implementation Planning Implications.

Phase Two, ITV Prototype and Testing. Using the outputs from phase one, this phase focuses on developing
and validating the core In-Transit Visibility (ITV) platform. The primary objective is to demonstrate the ability to
ingest, fuse, and visualize data from a variety of sources to create a Common Operating Picture (COP). It will
consist of three to five Commercial-Off-The-Shelf (COTS) and Government-Off-The-Shelf (GOTS) solutions,
including the Naval Autonomous Data Collection System (NADACS) and the Marine Corps Platform Integration
Center (MCPIC). These experimentation events will involve multi-modal, shipments from the Continental United
States (CONUS) to various outside the Continental United States (OCONUS).

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                       FY 2025    FY 2026
Phase Three, Full-Spectrum Asset Visibility (AV), Warehousing and Advanced Analytics. Building on the ITV
prototype, this phase expands the solution's scope to include visibility of assets at rest and integrates advanced
analytical capabilities. The goal is to create a single, unified platform for managing the entire logistics lifecycle,
from the warehouse shelf to the tactical edge.
