C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                      FY 2025     FY 2026      FY 2027
Title: International Cooperative Research and Development                                                                                    2.214       4.532        2.320
Description: Supports bi- and multi-lateral international agreements that meet the Department of the Air Force Research,
Development, Test, and Evaluation objectives and goals. Each of the projects receiving NATO Research and Development (R&D)
funding must meet 2 or more of the following requirements: enhance warfighter capabilities; increase coalition interoperability;
accelerate the availability of defense systems; strengthen coalition partnerships; gain access to the best technologies, capabilities,
techniques, and/or facilities/test ranges; build or sustain partnerships/influence with strategically important nations; and eliminate
duplication of R&D efforts.

FY 2026 Plans:
Continue FY 2025 projects and initiate new FY 2026 International Cooperative Research and Development (ICR&D) projects
focused on: quantum, photonic, electromagnetic enabling technology; system performance; materials for extreme environments;
collaborative combat aircraft; secure and resilient tactical communications; prediction of weapons effects; green propulsion and
power; space-based solar power; radio frequency interference; satellite continuity; corrosion prevention materials; synthetic
biology; cognitive modeling; and accelerated combined effects simulation. Bilateral and multilateral ICR&D cooperative
agreements, in the above areas, include cooperation with: Australia, France, Germany, India, Israel, Italy, Japan, Netherlands,
Singapore, Sweden, and the United Kingdom.
FY 2027 Plans:
Continue FY2026 activities and initiate FY 2027 International Cooperative Research and Development (ICR&D) projects focused
on: quantum, photonic; electromagnetic technology; space system performance; materials for extreme environments; collaborative
combat aircraft; secure and resilient tactical communications; weapons effects; propulsion and power; satellite continuity;
corrosion prevention; and hypersonic weapons. Bilateral and multilateral ICR&D cooperative agreements, in the above areas, are
with the following countries: Australia, Canada, Denmark, Israel, Italy, Japan, Netherlands, Singapore, Sweden, and the United
Kingdom.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Funding was decreased $2.275 between FY 2026 and FY 2027 is due to under execution.
