A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This program supports Department of War (DoW) priorities for Aerospace Systems demonstrations to include high-speed systems and autonomous collaborative
platforms through integration by design and starting with desired mission effect to deliver war winning capabilities to defend the homeland, provide nuclear deterrence,
and deliver force projection. System level integration and demonstration of advanced aerospace system and weapon technologies (autonomy, propulsion, power and
thermal, air vehicle, fuels, etc.) in a near-realistic operational environment to enhance the performance and supportability of existing and future aerospace systems
while reducing the risk and time required to transition technologies into operational platforms. Additionally, this program supports the nuclear enterprise and nuclear
deterrence through advanced components and technology demonstrations.

-The program focuses on technologies with a high potential to enhance the performance of existing and future Air Force weapon systems via modeling, simulation, and
analysis while utilizing digital engineering to accelerate and enhance S&T development.

-Missile Rocket Propulsion Integration and Demonstration: Develops and demonstrates innovative rocket propulsion technologies, propellants, and manufacturing
techniques for strategic and tactical systems to reduce costs, schedule, and increase performance.



