Note
The Next Generation Adaptive Propulsion effort consists of six phases: initial design, preliminary design, prototype planning, detailed design, prototype fabrication, and
engine assessments. Initial and preliminary activities were completed in 1Q FY2023. Prototype planning and detailed design activities were completed in 2Q FY 2025.
Delivery orders for prototype fabrication and engine assessments were awarded in 2Q FY 2025.

 Program deliverables include military adaptive engine detailed design parameters and models; engine hardware (plus spare parts); matured technologies; major rig
 assessment data (controls, combustor, etc.); program reviews; and technology, affordability and sustainment studies for capability enabling an embedded propulsion
 system that can be augmented for future fighters or non-augmented for other aircraft operating across various mission threads providing options for future Next
 Generation Air Dominance (NGAD) family of systems capabilities.

 Additional details can be provided in the appropriate forum.




