       Change Summary Explanation
       The decrease in FY 2024 from the Previous President's Budget to the Current President's Budget is due to a combination of Congressional marks that included a
       reduction for prior year carryover and inadequate justification and Congressional Adds for Space Sensor Fusion, Defense of Low Earth Orbit (LEO) Satellites, and
       Defense in Depth as Mission Assurance Spacecraft Multi-Level Security (DiDaMAS-MLS), and realignment for SBIR/STTR.

       The increase in FY 2025 from the Previous President's Budget to the Current President's Budget is due to Congressional Adds of Defense of LEO Satellites,
       DiDaMAS-MLS, Proliferated Warfighter Space Architecture (PWSA) Integrated Targeting Solution, Transport Layer Software Architecture, and Very High
       Frequency (VHF) Payload Satellite Demonstration.

       The decrease in FY 2026 from the Previous President's Budget to the Current President's Budget is due to adjustments for other United States Space Force
       priorities.

       The FY 2026 request was reduced by $6.781 million for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the policies of the Administration
       in alignment with Executive Order 14222, "Implementing the President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative."

