                                                                                                                         FY 2024      FY 2025
FY 2024 Accomplishments: Rapidly prototyped, evaluated, and iterated on a product that provided human
operators with an enhanced human-machine interface (HMI) designed and integrated to facilitate real-time
monitoring and alert operators to emerging threats to low earth orbit satellite systems. Refined machine learning
(ML) models created to monitor satellite telemetry data for threat induced anomaly detection in bus and mission
payload systems. Integrated these capabilities into operational systems providing actionable information for
comprehensive triage and response management by space operators.
FY 2025 Plans: Rapidly prototype, evaluate, and iterate on a product that provides human operators with an
enhanced human-machine interface (HMI) designed and integrated to facilitate real-time monitoring and alert
operators to emerging threats to low Earth orbit satellite systems. Refine ML models and integrate capabilities
into operational systems providing actionable information for comprehensive triage and response management
by space operators. Execute field tests at various ranges that can create the expected threat environments.
Congressional Add: Defense-in-Depth as Mission Assurance Spacecraft Multi-Level Security                                    2.890       20.000
FY 2024 Accomplishments: Researched and recommended a multi-level security (MLS) solution that securely
shares information across data sources on space vehicles with different classification levels to improve the
warfighter's ability to seize and maintain the initiative on the battlefield. Provided the USSF and other Service
tactical forces with the situational awareness required to recognize, coordinate, and exploit fleeting battlespace
opportunities that propagate from confined engagements into operational and strategic level effects. Work
included comparative advantage assessment of use of on-orbit MLS over ground-based solutions, researching
most mature solutions available from industry and determining their suitability for incorporation in the Proliferated
Warfighter Space Architecture (PWSA), and developing requirements specifications and a reference architecture
defining the most viable near-term approach for capability procurement and integration.
FY 2025 Plans: Refine ground station network architectures and designs, including NEBULA, BMC, and space
vehicle architectures. Develop tailored grading criteria on the latest NSA accreditation requirements. Collect
and evaluate MLS solutions against established criteria. Engage SDA POCs to gather further insights into future
Tranche MLS missions and operational needs. Perform market research on MLS technologies to inform ongoing
strategic decisions. Propose MLS frameworks, based on the research, to secure sensitive mission data. Ensure
secure data sharing between SDA, vendors, and testing facilities. Support SDA in designing and testing MLS
solutions for real-time space-based sensor fusion across classification levels.
