FY 2026 Plans:
The GRIFFON program will transition to the Execution Phase of the Software Acquisition Pathway which will begin a critical year
for integration and testing across the entire ESS architecture, to include all Ground software applications, framework, terminals,
operating locations, and test sites.

Mature ESS ground framework and integration prototype, Ground Integration and Framework (GIF), System of Systems
Integration (SoSI). The GIF/SoSI vendor will define and develop the Ground Assembly, Integration, and Test (Ground AI&T)
minimum viable product (MVP) and run the integration test with all ESS vendors and system capability in FY 2026, with a
projected exit of Ground AI&T in FY 2027. The Ground AI&T milestone will be the defining event that will encapsulate, integrate,
and test all of ESS Ground's individual software applications and capabilities into the system architecture. The Ground AI&T
milestone is the first integration test on the road to Initial Operational Capability (IOC), immediately preceding the next integration
milestone testing for System AI&T in FY 2028. System AI&T will include testing Ground with the Space, Crypto, and Terminal
segments, and will ensure that the system is interoperable and capable to enter into integrated launch testing.

The Mission Planning prototype will be down-selected from two to one vendor and then will be integrated with the space, crypto,
terminal, and ground framework segments. The Mission Planning prototype will then begin integrating with operational users
at operational locations and building test and training applications with the GIF/SoSI vendor. All integration issues found during
Ground AI&T testing will be fixed in FY 2026 in an agile ramp up to ensure software is mission capable upon exit of Ground AI&T
in FY 2027.

The Out-of-Band Command and Control (OOB-C2) software application vendors will consolidate the operational user interface
between legacy and resiliency application components, and begin testing in an operationally relevant environment.

The In-Band Command and Control (IB-C2) software application will begin testing with the Ground Framework and other mission
applications. IB-C2 will begin integration efforts and testing in the operational environment and the selected ESS Command and
Control (C2) terminals.

The ESS C2 Terminal that completes the IB-C2 architecture will begin integration testing in an operationally relevant environment.
The ESS C2 Terminals will be modernized for cryptographic, cybersecurity, resiliency, survivability, and interoperabilty
requirements, necessary to support ESS and meet critical ground segment, space segment, and systems integration need dates.
ESS must enter Ground Assembly, Integration and Test in FY 2026 to meet the USSTRATCOM threat-driven strategic need date

