existing data centers to support Artificial Intelligence (AI) capabilities. This strategy maximizes current infrastructure investments to deliver advanced data analytics and
autonomous planning tools across all classification networks, actively avoiding the high costs and extended timelines associated with existing time-intensive tasks such
as drafting operation plans, summarizing intelligence, and integrating cross domain data.

This approach focuses on improving on-premises infrastructure to support DoW scalable environments, data analytics, and AI tool suites to support the integration
of intelligence, planning, and operations data to address immediate mission needs. For example, this capability provides analysts with instant access to AI driven
dashboards and alerts that fuse sensor feeds, logistics, and mission plans to rapidly enhance border monitoring, illicit trafficking detection, and domain awareness which
significantly reduces analytic workloads, accelerates operational planning, and drives decision superiority in direct support of Homeland Defense (HD) and the Unified
Command Plan (UCP).

Under the Unified Command Plan, USNORTHCOM must maintain decision superiority by delivering timely, data-driven insights to protect the homeland. The current
manual analytic workloads and extended planning cycles severely limit the response time to emerging threats. This AI implementation directly addresses limiting factors
by streamlining analytic workloads, shrinking plan-drafting cycles, and drastically boosting real-time warning accuracy for border incursions, missile launches, and illicit
trafficking. Embedding agentic AI directly into staff processes and coordination workflows accelerates situational awareness and tightens critical decision timelines,
unlocking additional capacity for high-value decision support.

This effort is in Budget Activity 4, Advanced Component Development and Prototypes (ACD&P), because efforts are necessary to evaluate integrated technologies,
representative modes or prototype systems in a high fidelity and realistic operating environment.




