Title: HACM Development                                                                                                                  425.983     764.099       717.220
Description: Encompasses the development effort on the program, outside of testing, and program support, to include enhancing
capabilities, additional prototype deliveries, industrial base investments towards full-rate production, and operational suitability
improvements.

FY 2026 Plans:
This effort continued model-based system engineering activities in the Digital Engineering (DE) ecosystem. Continued efforts
included additional design verification testing, operational suitability improvements, prototype manufacturing, systems integration,
subsystem qualification, manufacturing capacity investment, and integration on the F-15E and F/A-18F platforms. Continued work
on product improvement for integration into design, development, and production.
FY 2027 Plans:
Purchase hardware and validate the HACM design to continue ground and flight test activities. Continue to purchase long-lead
flight test asset hardware and make investment in manufacturing readiness and operational suitability improvements.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The decrease of $46.879 million is due to the program closing critical design activities.
Title: Integration, Qualification, and Test                                                                                              26.817       63.976         88.922
Description: This effort includes the Government costs associated with assembly, integration and test of subsystems for
qualification testing as well as prototype systems for system qualification, ground test and flight testing. The effort includes the
planning, execution and analysis to complete the defined HACM test strategy.

FY 2026 Plans:
Effort conducted additional subsystem qualification testing and integration, assembly, test, and checkout of the All-Up Round
system. Efforts included initial flight testing of HACM prototypes and other risk data.
FY 2027 Plans:
Effort will continue subsystem qualification testing and the integration, assembly, test, and checkout of the All-Up Round system.
Efforts will also include flight testing of HACM prototypes and other risk data.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The increase of $24.946M is due to the program adding integration and test activities as well as the execution of All-Up-Round
flight verification tests.
