C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                FY 2025     FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: SAOC                                                                                                                            0.000   1,801.293     2,218.921
Description: The SAOC weapon system is comprised of a Commercial Derivative Aircraft (CDA), mission system, and ground
support systems. The CDA will be hardened to protect against nuclear and electromagnetic effects and modified with an aerial
refueling capability to enable sustained airborne operations. The mission system will integrate secure communications and
planning capabilities on modern information technology (IT) infrastructure based on a Modular Open System Approach (MOSA).
The ground systems include aircrew trainers, mission crew trainers, maintenance training devices, ground support equipment,
test and sustainment system integration laboratories, and other ground systems to enable the operations, sustainment, and future
modifications of the SAOC weapon system across the lifecycle.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue executing Engineering and Manufacturing Development (EMD) design activities to include system engineering, trade
studies, system/subsystem engineering analysis and preliminary design for the aircraft, mission system, training systems, and
supporting systems
- Continue supporting development, modernization, and delivery of required Nuclear Command, Control, and Communications
(NC3), Command, Control, and Communications (C3), Cryptographic, OA/OMS, and other mission system capabilities to ensure

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                       FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
systems are sustainable and available to integrate into the EMD design and overall SAOC Weapon System (to include FAB-T
CPT)
- Continue to refine and implement the infrastructure, tools, and training necessary for the SAOC Integrated Digital Environment
and program execution, enabling the SAOC Program Office to continue to execute and support the development and lifecycle
sustainment of the SAOC Weapon System
- Continue Test and Evaluation (T&E) execution planning and preparation activities including manning, procurement of test
equipment, training, and facility modifications; continue early functional testing at the component and Line Replaceable Unit (LRU)
levels; continue development of the T&E System Integration Laboratory (SIL)
- Reach and maintain program office manning required to support the SAOC system development
- Continue coordination activities with appropriate stakeholders to ensure that SAOC requirements are properly accounted for, and
integrated, within facilities currently under development
- Continue Product Support Business Case Analysis (PS-BCA) to support Product Support strategies to achieve SAOC
capabilities and affordability
- Continue follow on Supply Chain Risk Management Analysis and Illumination
FY 2027 Plans:
- Continue executing Engineering and Manufacturing Development (EMD) design activities to include system engineering, trade
studies, system/subsystem engineering analysis, preliminary design and critical design for the aircraft, mission system, training
systems, and supporting systems
- Continue Mission System EMD development, modernization, and delivery of required Nuclear Command, Control, and
Communications (NC3), Command, Control, and Communications (C3), Cryptographic, Open Architecture / Open Mission
Systems (OA/OMS), software, workstations, mission system infrastructure, and other mission system capabilities to ensure
systems are sustainable and available to integrate into the EMD design and overall SAOC Weapon System
- Continue executing EMD design activities to include system engineering and system/subsystem design reviews, manufacturing
readiness and quality assurance as part of the Preliminary Design Review Process.
- Continue to refine and implement the infrastructure, tools, and training necessary for the SAOC Integrated Digital Environment
and program execution, enabling the SAOC Program Office to continue to execute and support the development and lifecycle
sustainment of the SAOC Weapon System
- Continue T&E execution activities including manning, procurement of test equipment, training, and facility modifications; continue
early functional testing at the component and Line Replaceable Unit (LRU) levels; continue development of the T&E SIL
- Continue executing Air Vehicle EMD design activities to include systems engineering, trade studies, system/subsystem
engineering analysis, risk reduction, prototyping, integration, survivability mandates, test readiness, preliminary design, and initial
critical design for the aircraft. Continue to execute Commercial Derivative Aircraft (CDA) Pre Ops Support activities to ensure
green aircraft availability to support continued EMD characterization, modification, test, certification, and delivery objectives

